  <section id="design" data-nav="design">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <div class="blankHXXS"></div>
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/divider25`, {
            sectionName:'Design',
            topSpacing:'spacingMedium',
            bottomSpacing:'spacingXLarge',
            topNbottomSpacing:''
            }) %>

            <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">
                  <h1 class="fontWeight400">Mental model mismatch</h1>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-3">

              <div class="Grid-cell displayDesktopTablet">
                <div class="element">
                  <img class="widthLogo" src="icon_traveler.svg" alt="">


                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="Grid-cell displayDesktopTablet">
                <div class="element">
                  <img class="widthLogo" src="icon_marketplace.svg" alt="">



                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="Grid-cell displayDesktopTablet">
                <div class="element">
                  <img class="widthLogo" src="icon_idea.svg" alt="">


                </div>
              </div>
            </div>



            <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-3">

              <div class="Grid-cell displayDesktopTablet">
                <div class="element">

                  <h6>User expectation</h6>

                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="Grid-cell displayDesktopTablet">
                <div class="element">

                  <h6> Marketplace reality</h6>

                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="Grid-cell displayDesktopTablet">
                <div class="element">

                  <h6> Design principle</h6>


                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-3">

              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">

                  <h6 class="fontWeight400">“I should know what I’m paying before I commit.”</h6>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">

                  <h6 class="fontWeight400">Pricing depends on which provider fulfills the order.</h6>

                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">

                  <h6 class="fontWeight400">Reduce false certainty.</h6>
                  <h6>Don’t let the UI imply that prices are final before the system actually knows them.</h6>

                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="spacingSmall"></div>
            <hr class="wrapperM">
            <div class="spacingMedium"></div>
            <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-3">

              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">

                  <h6 class="fontWeight400">“I came from Vrbo. I already told you where I’m staying.”</h6>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">

                  <h6 class="fontWeight400">Users arrive in an embedded BabyQuip experience with little context about what’s happening.</h6>

                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">

                  <h6 class="fontWeight400">Clarify context before action.</h6>
                  <h6>Show where they are, what information carried over from Vrbo, and why they can trust the next step.</h6>

                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="spacingSmall"></div>
            <hr class="wrapperM">
            <div class="spacingMedium"></div>


            <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-3">

              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">

                  <h6 class="fontWeight400">“I’ve added everything I need. I’m basically ready to book.”</h6>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">

                  <h6 class="fontWeight400">A provider still hasn’t been selected, so the booking isn’t actually ready.</h6>

                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">

                  <h6 class="fontWeight400">Make commitment visible at the right moment.</h6>
                  <h6>Instead of encouraging endless browsing, clearly guide users toward provider selection, because that’s the real commitment point.</h6>

                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="spacingSmall"></div>
            <hr class="wrapperM">
            <div class="spacingMedium"></div>
            <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-3">

              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">

                  <h6 class="fontWeight400">“I’m checking out.”</h6>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">

                  <h6 class="fontWeight400">The flow asks users to repeat information and make decisions they’ve already made.</h6>

                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">

                  <h6 class="fontWeight400">Remove repeated decisions.</h6>
                  <h6>Reduce unnecessary screens so the experience feels like one continuous path to checkout.</h6>

                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
    



            <div class="spacingXLarge"></div>

            <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="element">
                  <h1 class="fontWeight400">Solutions</h1>
                  <h4>Because pricing and availability could not be finalized before provider selection, the redesign made that uncertainty visible through contextual messaging instead of letting the UI imply false certainty.</h4>
                </div>

              </div>
              <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
                <div class="Grid-cell">
                  <div class="element">
                    <h3 class="fontWeight400">1. <span class="fontWeight500">Entry:</span> clarify context on arrival (Vrbo-specific)</h3>
                    <div class="marginLeft">
                      <ul class="listCircle">
                        <li>Reduce system interruptions at entry</li>
                        <li>Surface trip details early so users understand what they are booking against</li>
                      </ul>
                      <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
                    </div>
                    <img class="modal-target card2026" src="design_pre_entry.png" alt="">
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

              <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
                <div class="Grid-cell">
                  <div class="element">
                    <h3 class="fontWeight400">2.<span class="fontWeight500">Shopping:</span> reduce false progress before provider selection (Vrbo-specific)</h3>
                    <div class="marginLeft">
                      <ul class="listCircle">
                        <li>De-emphasize placeholder pricing and incomplete item certainty</li>
                        <li>Reframe add-to-cart as a transition, not a completion moment</li>
                        <li>Guide users from browsing toward provider selection as the next required step</li>
                      </ul>
                      <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
                    </div>
                    <img class="modal-target card2026" src="design_shopping.png" alt="">

                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

              <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
                <div class="Grid-cell">
                  <div class="element">
                    <h3 class="fontWeight400">3. <span class="fontWeight500">Commitment:</span> make provider selection explicit at the right moment (cross-platform)</h3>
                    <div class="marginLeft">
                      <ul class="listCircle">
                        <li>Make provider selection visible and necessary</li>
                        <li>Reduce dead-end cart states before fulfillment is confirmed</li>
                        <li>Align user actions with provider-based marketplace logic</li>
                      </ul>
                      <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
                    </div>
                    <img class="modal-target card2026" src="design_select_provider.png" alt="">

                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

              <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
                <div class="Grid-cell">
                  <div class="element">
                    <h3 class="fontWeight400">4. <span class="fontWeight500">Pre-checkout:</span> remove redundant decision states (cross-platform)</h3>
                    <div class="marginLeft">
                      <ul class="listCircle">
                        <li>Remove repeated decision states across cart, add-ons, and summary</li>
                        <li>Make checkout the dominant action once users are ready to commit</li>
                        <li>Consolidate add-ons, order summary, and checkout into one continuous path</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>

                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-2">
                <div class="Grid-cell">
                  <div class="element">
                    <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_pre_checkout.png" alt="">

                    <h4><span class="fontWeight400">Before:</span> fragmented flow with repeated decision states before checkout</h4>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="Grid-cell">
                  <div class="element">
                    <img class="modal-target card2026" src="design_pre_checkout.png" alt="">

                    <h4><span class="fontWeight400">After:</span> one continuous path from add-ons to checkout</h4>

                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>

            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

  </section>

  <section id="impact" data-nav="impact">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <div class="blankHXXS"></div>
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/divider25`, {
            sectionName:'Impact',
            topSpacing:'spacingMedium',
            bottomSpacing:'spacingXLarge',
            topNbottomSpacing:''
            }) %>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h1 class="fontWeight400">Impact</h1>
            <h4>The redesign improved early-funnel progression and purchase completion directionally, while also revealing the deeper structural tension between gear-first browsing and provider-first fulfillment.</h6>
              <div class="spacingMedium"></div>
              <h5 class="fontWeight500">Reduce Discovery and Shopping Drop-Off</h5>
              <div class="marginLeft">
                <ul class="listCircle">
                  <li>Maintained gear context as travelers moved from Vrbo into BabyQuip. General entry points display Vrbo and BabyQuip branding, while gear-specific entry points preserve the selected item.</li>
                  <li>Replaced the disruptive trip-information modal with a lightweight popover confirming that the traveler’s address carried over from Vrbo.</li>
                  <li>Simplified the privacy settings prompt with a clearer path to continue.</li>
                  <li>Adjusted disclaimer explaining that displayed prices may change after provider selection.</li>
                  <li>Highlighted the Vrbo traveler discount while removing unrelated app-download messaging.</li>
                  <li>Improved filter visibility and navigation so travelers can find and compare gear more easily.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <h5 class="fontWeight500">Increase Checkout Progression</h5>
              <div class="marginLeft">
                <ul class="listCircle">
                  <li>Consolidated the cart-to-checkout journey from three or four screens to two, removing repeated steps across platforms.</li>
                  <li>Improved the order summary and pricing breakdown so travelers can proceed to checkout with greater confidence.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-2">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5 class="fontWeight400">Before launch: Mar 25–Apr 24 (30 days)</h5>
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="ga4_before_launch.png" alt="Vrbo mobile vs non-Vrbo mobile">
          </div>

        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5 class="fontWeight400">After launch: May 17–Jun 15 (30 days)</h5>
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="ga4_after_launch.png" alt="Vrbo mobile vs Vrbo web">
          </div>
        </div>


      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3>Observed funnel changes</h3>
            <div class="marginLeft">

              <ul class="listCircle">
                <li>Entry - Shopping: <span class="fontWeight400">+60%</span></li>
                <li>Shopping - Add to Cart: <span class="fontWeight400">+5.5%</span></li>
                <li>Add to Cart - Cart View: <span class="fontWeight400">+21%</span></li>
                <li>Cart - Checkout: <span class="fontWeight400">-28%</span></li>
                <li>Purchase: <span class="fontWeight400 colorbg">+98% directional</span></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
            <h5 class="csCallout">
              Cart → Checkout: -28%, not directly comparable after flow changes because the redesign reduced repeated cart/order-summary loops.
            </h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>




      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h1 class="fontWeight400">Trade-offs</h1>

            <div class="marginLeft">
              <ul class="listCircle">
                <li><span class="fontWeight400">Did not resolve the provider-first vs gear-first model tension</span>: users still browse before fulfillment is fully known</li>
                <li><span class="fontWeight400">Placeholder item logic remains</span>: pricing and availability still become reliable only after provider selection</li>
                <li>Did not enable provider selection without items (explored but not shipped)</li>
                <li>Limited by embedded webview + tracking gaps</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h1 class="fontWeight400">What this did not solve</h1>

            <h4 class="fontWeight400">Future direction:</h4>
            <h5>Longer term, the better structural fix is a dual-entry model that supports both browse-first and provider-first journeys.</h5>
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="design_dual-entry_model.png" alt="Provider selection available before item selection">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

  </section>
